ENTRY            A0651   20260206   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0651001   20260206   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 11         44
TITLE      Stellar reaction rate of 14N(p,gamma)15O and
           hydrogen burning in massive stars
AUTHOR     (U.Schroeder, H.W.Becker, G.Bogaert, J.Goerres,
           C.Rolfs, H.P.Trautvetter, R.E.Auma, C.Campbell,
           J.D.King, J.Vise)
INSTITUTE  (2GERMST,1CANTOR)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,467,240,1987)
           (T,SCHROEDER,1987) Data tables were taken from the
           thesis
FACILITY   (CCW,2GERMST) Supplied a proton beam of up to 320 uA
           in the energy range 180-350 keV. Error of energy
           calibration < 1 keV and beam energy spread < 0.5 keV.
           (VDG,1CANTOR) was used for the energy range 270-1100
           keV with beam current of up 160 uA. Beam energy
           spread < 1 keV, error of energy calibration < 2 keV.
           (DYNAM,2GERBOC) Supplied a proton beam of up 40 uA in
           the energy range 800-3600 keV. Error of energy
           calibration 0.04% and energy spread < 3 keV.
METHOD     (GSPEC,SITA)
DETECTOR   (GELI)
SAMPLE     For one set of experiments at the 350 keV accelerator
           Ti-N solid targets were used. The targets, 10 keV,
           approximately, thick at 280 keV, were produced by
           evaporating a thin layer of Ti onto a thick Ta
           backing and nitriding the Ti layer in a nitrogen
           atmosphere by resistance heating. In the experiments
           at the 350 keV accelerator windowless gas target
           systems of the extended type or of the quasi-point
           supersonic Jet Type were used too. At the
           energy > 0.4 MeV 14N ions were implanted in 0.1 mm
           thick Ta sheets.
ADD-RES    (STRUC) Of some levels of 15O.
COMMENT    All energy values were taken from level structure shown
           on fig.4 of the thesis (same on fig.1 of the article).
HISTORY    (20000211C)
           (20000717A) Date is corrected.
           (20090827A) Correction in author' list has been done,
           according to V.Zerkin remarks.
           Correction in Subents 002-020, according to new EXFOR
           rules. Subent 017 was split into two.
           (20100111A) Correction in date subent 002, according
           to M.Bossant remarks.
           (20260206A) SD: Corrections in all Subents. Several
           Subents were merged.
ENDBIB              44
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           47
SUBENT        A0651002   20260206   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                  6         16
REACTION   (7-N-14(P,G)8-O-15,PAR,SIG)
REL-REF    (R,,C.Rolfs,J,NP/A,217,29,1973)
           (R,,H.W.Becker+,J,ZP/A,308,73,1982)
COMMENT    - By Authors - The cross section of direct capture to
           6.79-MeV state was determined as 580 +/- 85 nb
           in REL-REF. U.Schroeder gives 720 +/- 140 nb in
           his thesis. The value in Data Section is weighted
           average of both measurements.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total error includes:
           (ERR-1) Experimental uncertainties
           (ERR-2) Individual uncertainties in each of the
           reference standards
STATUS     (TABLE,,U.Schroeder,J,NP/A,467,240,1987) Value from
           the text on p.254
HISTORY    (20260206A) SD: BIB updated. DATA-ERR -> ERR-T.
           ERR-ANALYS updated. COMMON added.
ENDBIB              16
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 6          1
EN         E-LVL      DATA       ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-T
MEV        MEV        NB         PER-CENT   PER-CENT   NB
      0.813      6.793       620.         8.        10.        80.
ENDDATA              3
ENDSUBENT           24
SUBENT        A0651003   20260206   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                  6         22
REACTION   (7-N-14(P,G)8-O-15,PAR,SIG,,SFC)
LEVEL-PROP (8-O-15,E-LVL=7.556,SPIN=0.5,PARITY=+1.)
           (8-O-15,E-LVL=7.276,SPIN=3.5,PARITY=+1.)
           (8-O-15,E-LVL=6.859,SPIN=2.5,PARITY=+1.)
           (8-O-15,E-LVL=6.793,SPIN=1.5,PARITY=+1.)
           (8-O-15,E-LVL=6.176,SPIN=1.5,PARITY=-1.)
           (8-O-15,E-LVL=5.241,SPIN=2.5,PARITY=+1.)
           (8-O-15,E-LVL=5.183,SPIN=0.5,PARITY=+1.)
           (8-O-15,E-LVL=0.,SPIN=0.5,PARITY=-1.)
FLAG       (1.) S-factor scale is invalid for resonances not much
           wider than the target thickness used.
           (2.) The value is shown in authors' data table.
ERR-ANALYS Total error includes:
           (ERR-1) Uncertainty in the absolute effective
           cross-section
           (ERR-2) Experimental uncertainty. The specified errors
           do not include the error of 13% for the absolute
           effective cross-section, so that this quadratic must
           be added.
STATUS     (TABLE,,U.Schroeder,T,SCHROEDER,1987) tbls on pp.73-80
HISTORY    (20260206A) SD: Data from Subents 004-010 were added.
           BIB updated. DATA-ERR -> ERR-2.
ENDBIB              22
COMMON               1          3
ERR-1
PER-CENT
